<text>Filling with color

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

The background of some components, e.g. embedded models and the page containing them, or shapes in a model, can be filled with color, texture, and image. This is generally done through the following pop-up menu:

  
[This is a screenshot.]

This menu is often deployed at the menu bar or tool bar for the component with changable background.

To fill the background with a single color, just select from the above menu a color from the color list. If none of the listed colors satisfies you, click the &quot;More Colors&quot;, and choose from the following dialog box:

  
[This is a screenshot.]

In the next sections, you will see that background can be filled with more than just a color.

